<br>
Very much so.  I moved from a high school in San Antonio, Texas known for academic excellence(Clark, if you're from there).  Then I ended up moving to Denver the middle of  my junior year.  Both schools are your average, run of the mill high school.  The quality of the teachers is the same, but the people just aren't interested in education, or going to college nearly as much as the people I knew at Clark.  The difference is family, and motivation-and the school can not do anything about that.<br>
<br>
Interestingly enough, Clark had a much higher percentage of athletes.  Wonder if that had anything to do with it, even with the extremely false 'dumb jock' stereotype.<br>
<br>
